<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-us" class="no-js">
	<%= render "main/partials/shared/head" %>

	<body>
		<%= render "main/partials/shared/nav" %>
    <section id="home-part" class="vegas-container right-home">
			<div class="overlay"></div>
		</section> <!-- CLOSE #home-part -->

		<section id="content-part" class="right-content">

      <div class="inner-content" style="padding-top: 0; border-top: 5px solid #08c; margin-top: -1px;">
				<div style="position: relative;">
					<div class="row">

						<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12">

              <div class="">
								<h3 class="story-title center">Dr. Derek M. Griffith, PhD</h3>
							</div>

							<div class="padding_top_20px story_image">
								<%= image_tag("bio/griffith.png", class: "center-image img-responsive img-rounded box-shadow-ccc") %>
							</div>

							<div class="">
								<p class="story_txt left lead">
                  Derek M. Griffith, PhD is Associate Professor of Medicine, Health and Society and Director of the Center for Research on Men’s Health at Vanderbilt University. Trained in clinical-community psychology and public health, Dr. Griffith primarily focuses on identifying and addressing psychological, social and cultural determinants of African American men’s health and unjust racial and ethnic differences in health; he also has begun examining and addressing of Latino men’s health. He specializes in using qualitative and quantitative research to identify how men approach and prioritize health behavior – particularly during middle-age – to inform and evaluate interventions to reduce men’s chronic disease risk and risk behaviors that can be tailored to their individual beliefs, attitudes, needs and preferences.  His research on African American and Latino men’s health has been funded by foundations such as the American Cancer Society and the Aetna Foundation and several institutes within the National Institutes of Health.
                </p>
							</div>

              <div class="col-sm-12 no_side_padding story_next_button">
                <div class="col-sm-6 no_side_padding">
                  <p class="pull-left back_arrow">
                    <%= link_to about_path, class: "skip_link" do %>
                      <i class="fa fa-long-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                      Return to About Page
                    <% end %>
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="col-sm-6 no_side_padding">
                  <div class="col-sm-12 no_side_padding">
                    <%= link_to "Learn About Dr. Laveist", bio_laveist_path, class: "btn btn-primary pull-right" %>
                  </div>
                </div>
							</div>

						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

		</section> <!-- CLOSE #content-part -->

	</body>

</html>
